    <h2>Help</h2>

    <h3>How do I create membership plans?</h3>

    <p>
      Simply click on the “Membership” tab and then click on the blue button that says “New Membership Plan”. Type in the name of your new membership plan, select either “Public” or “Invite Only”, set up the frequency of recurring payment, and then enter the fee. Once you are done, click “Create”.
    </p>

    <h3>What’s the difference between “Public” and “Invite Only” membership plans?</h3>

    <p>
      Public membership plans will be visible to those who have access to your public invite link. Invite Only membership plans will be hidden from the public link, and your members can only access it if you send out an invite via the “Invite Someone” button.
    </p>

    <h3>I collect payments bi-weekly. Is it possible to set up recurring payment for every two weeks?</h3>

    <p>
      Unfortunately, the only options for our membership plans are annually, quarterly, monthly, or weekly. We would recommend that you select the monthly option.
    </p>

    <h3>How do I edit my membership plans?</h3>

    <p>
      Simply click on the setting, and you will be able to change the name of your membership, public access or delete the membership.
    </p>

    <h3>Can I change the amount charged for my membership plan?</h3>

    <p>
      The easiest way to change the amount charged for your membership plan is to delete it and create a new one. This is to ensure that your billing cycle doesn’t get messed up.
    </p>

